name: Leg Press
details: A compound lower-body exercise done on a leg press machine. It primarily targets the quadriceps, hamstrings, and glutes, making it effective for building leg strength and muscle mass.

name: Dumbbell Press
details: A strength training exercise where you press dumbbells overhead while seated or standing. It targets the shoulders, triceps, and upper chest, enhancing upper body strength and stability.

name: Chest Press
details: Performed on a bench using dumbbells or a barbell, the chest press focuses on the pectoral muscles, triceps, and shoulders. It's great for building upper body strength and muscle mass.

name: Lat Pulldown
details: A strength training exercise performed on a cable machine. It targets the latissimus dorsi (back muscles), biceps, and shoulders, helping to build a wide and strong back.

name: Hammer Strength
details: A machine-based workout designed to simulate free weight exercises. It offers controlled movements for targeting specific muscle groups, such as chest, back, or shoulders, while minimizing joint strain.

name: Fly Press
details: An isolation exercise performed on a bench with dumbbells or a machine. It focuses on the chest muscles by mimicking a hugging motion, helping to develop a broad and defined chest

name: Abdominal Roller
details: A core-strengthening tool that uses a wheel with handles to perform roll-outs. This exercise engages the abs, obliques, and lower back, improving core stability and strength.

name: Weight Lifting
details: A general term for exercises involving lifting weights, including free weights (like barbells and dumbbells) and machines. It targets various muscle groups, promoting strength, muscle growth, and overall fitness.
